skyrim is the latest installment in bugthesdas legendary elder scrolls franchisegames which have always been touted as genre defining & it pleases me to say that skyrim is no exception with its barren vast open world landscape & its cast of interesting characters skyrim is the definitive rpg experience that you will ever get to play in order to elaborate on this i am now going to give you the reasons as to why you should get the elder scrolls v skyrim pros flying mammoths gorgeous game world with 512 x 512 & 256 x 256 textures  1024 x 1024 with the hd texture pack  excellent companion ai that hinder quests by stepping on to traps as well as triggering them for you in order to make you feel more immersed in the game as well as blocking doorways & always being spotted by the enemy especially if you want to roleplay as a sneaky character this is another feature that makes you feel more immersed no dependence on mods unlike the other games in the franchise skyrim is not dependent on mods to keep it interesting even after 300 hours of gameplay cause who doesnt love replaying the same opening sequence for the 6th time easy & glitchy dragon fights who needs challenging boss battles when we can just kill dragons & feel like gods screw timing & skill required in your average game boss fights skyrim did it right so much so that you dont even have to lift a finger in most fights you can just let the other npcs handle it for you its not like the game says that you are the only one who can kill the dragons broken quests this is the most important feature of the game as it encourages the player to keep playing the game again & again in order to complete that quest and at times it also forces the player to delete saves & hence reducing progress you have made so far in the gamethis further increases your game time bugthesda are one of the true pioneers of this feature & other games have also started adopting this paid mods is the latest innovation that bugthesda in collaboration with valve have brought to the table for skyrim although skyrim is not dependent on mods but it is still a good option for the players cause who doesnt want to pay for something that may or may not work & could possibly harm your saved game to be honest i cant think of a single con for this game cause its just so perfect and i think i have made that very clear with the features mentioned above i think my only gripe would be that the soundtrack is just so meh in my humble opinion final verdict  1110 skyrim is a game that definitely deserved the critical acclaim that it got back in 2011 although it was released in the same year that saw games like i dont know deus ex human revolution batman arkham city dark souls uncharted 3 witcher 2 but hey those games dont stand a chance against skyrim & all of its innovative feautures a clear goty winner
