the elder scrolls v skyrim is an openworld rpg with an awesome story and it has one of the biggest world to explore in any games ever made in this game you play as the dragonborn the chosen one that is meant to protect skyrim from dragons honestly the elder scrolls v skyrim is probably one of the best game on steam the ambiance and everything is just so great its still one of the best selling games on steam even 3 years after its release if you havent played it yet and are you not sure if you should buy it you can check my personal score below category rating 10 details gameplay 81 the game is very well designed you can set hotkeys for multiple spells or weapons at once you can do questlines and misc quests at any times as long as you have the requirements theres tons of content to explore the elder scrolls v skyrim doesnt offer anything new to the genre however and its not very well balanced some dragons are easier to kill than some types of undeads found in dungeons also the ai can be quite confusing sometimes monsters stands still and let you kill them sometimes enemies do not even notice you walking in front of them with a high stealth level everybody can play the game due to good difficulty settings but keep in mind the controls are poor and theres some weird balance going on graphics 80 the elder scrolls v skyrim graphics are nice some things like snow and npcs are not very appealing but during the time you play you will find tons of amazing landscapes skies buildings and forests thats for the base game of course because you can make the game more beautiful with mods as for the animations most are fine but rolling and ragdoll deaths are not so well done the interface is simple and has just the right amount of information atmosphere 85 the music is totally amazing it really fits the game fighting music is intense and while exploring the music really sets the atmosphere sound effects are alright though repetitive my opinion on voice acting is a bit more complex though honestly i am impressed by some characters voice acting like cicero astrid senera sheogorath they have very unique and amazing voices on the other hand some npcs shares the same voice like litterally not just the same voice actor but the same actual voice in game on multiple npcs performance 48 heres the weak point of the game definately the amount of bugs is just catastrophic i could write a paragraph longer than this review to list all the bugs ive experienced while playing the elder scrolls v skyrim for around 140 hours game breaking bugs where you cannot complete certain quest and hope that you can complete them with the console sometimes you need to restart the entire game from the start if you absolutely need to complete a certain quest your character can fall through the floor monsters fall from the sky randomly playing at higher than 60 fps will cause your game to act weird some areas will just make your game crash upon loading i know that the mod skyrim unofficial patches can be downloaded to fix some of these issues but with the game as is you are going to be annoyed really quickly with the tons of bugs you will encounter during your playthrough of the game as for the overall performance the game runs quite smoothly at 60 fps at least story 92 the story is another very strong point of the elder scrolls v skyrim some questlines in particular will get you so addicted to the game that you will play it through until its done the fact that almost all of your choices affects the outcome and scenario of almost every single quests is just crazy the amount of work put into this aspect of the game is huge you can be a good guy a bad guy or simply do just what you want a certain character annoys you kill him you recovered a powerful artifact that somebody asked you to get for him if you want to keep it you can thats how much you can control your characters fate singleplayer 85 well since the elder scrolls v skyrim only offers singleplayer this is just a resume of my review the game is fun to play by yourself it doesnt get boring at all and its totally worth trying out just keep in mind that bugs and crashes will affect your experience by a large margin unless you mod your game heavily even there you might still experience some annoying bugs with mods but its definately gonna be better multiplayer  this game features no coop or multiplayer playtime 10 the game is known for excelling in this aspect it took me 140 hours just to go through essensial parts of the game to complete all achievements i have only done a few questlines and theres tons and tons of misc quests that i have not started just in 1 playthrough you can spend from 100 to upward of 1000 hours depending on many quests you wanna finish you many things you want to personally accomplish and if you want to craft full sets of gear get to a very high level unlock all magics find all books etc replayability is definately a strong point too you can create a new character to try out a different race look build or just to redo some questlines you might want to approach differently because your choices in some quests will completely affect what happens during and after the quest prices 90 for the amount of content and playtime this game offers us$1999 as of late 2014 is a steal sure the dlcs are quite expansive but if you get the legendary edition for us$3999 you will get much more content and a better price than individual dlcs by far this game is totally worth buying at the listed price steam features 10 its got all the features you would hope for the achievements in this game are super fun to work towards with only a few missable ones that you can easily manage to do if you readup well enough before starting your game its got trading cards and most important steam workshop support as of late 2014 there are over 23000 gameplay mods items quests creatures the list goes on the modding community is extremely active for the elder scrolls v skyrim its also got partial controller support and steam cloud game score 81 information hours details time required to complete the game 30 hours main questline  few misc quests and item farming time required to fully complete the game 1000 hours all quests  collect items  max level in all skills etc time required to get 100% achievements in the game 140 hours 7575 achievements working no particulary hard achievements
