the elder scrolls iv oblivion is the greatest game ive played i dont think i will ever enjoy a game as much again the euphoric high was that strong because it was a masterpiece it took my breath away the elder scrolls v skyrim deserves to be the next installment of the series and the follow up to such a sublime work of art it draws on the formula that made oblivion great yet uses that formula in its own unique way to create a world that you can explore that is different from the story the cultures the customs and civilizations found in oblivions cyrodiil province there are a multitude of major and minor quests that guide you in exploring skyrim these missions whether they are mini stories or extended quest lines intrigue the player into exploring further some tales are witty others tragic and sometimes they are both this results in the quest outcomes producing an emotional response of some form for the player the quest stories are a great collection of journeys to follow but the finest moments in this game are probably those that are unscripted for instance my party of four was walking on the forest road passing close to largashbur an orc camp when a random bear attacked the group even my horse got stuck in to the bear riftens road patrol guards came to our aid as well shortly after that a civil war enemy faction who must have been close by suddenly attacked the guards later a massive fire breathing dragon then swooped down from the skies and he didnt care who he picked on at some point i must have gotten too close to largashbur which triggered a quest involving a giant who then attacks the orc camp that in itself is a big battle but the two scrimmages became one the chaos was such i have no idea who was on whose side after that a second fire breathing dragon arrived and he was attacking the giant as well other forest creatures such as giant spiders became opportunists too this fight went on for an extended period of time but i remember a moment seeing my horse terrified fleeing through the forest trees burning pursued by a flying dragon i thought to myself you cant script this in oblivion drakes were fantastic adversaries but one thing missing were dragons prior to skyrim i had always hoped a sequel to oblivion would introduce dragons creatures that were much bigger more powerful fearsome and majestic looking skyrim didnt just deliever it became the benchmark they are beyond what i had hoped for further to this the integration of the greybeards dragon shouts etc into skyrims dragon lore both as a storyline and in gameplay was a great accomplishment in itself as well the official hearthfire dlc was another aspect of skyrim that improved on what was a fantatic feature in oblivion the standard houses in skyrim are a little bland compared to those in oblivion but the hearthfire dlc changed that around it is a wonderful progression in the elder scrolls series i am however still wanting more from this aspect of the game if there is an elder scrolls vi i anticipate they will work on that further skyrim is amazing for its library of mods ive never seen such a diverse range of mods for a game which doesnt mean much for i play very few games i found some quirks of the standard game irritating but if i want some aspect of skyrim changed theres going to be a mod to resolve it i conjured dead thralls which would constantly groan and it gets annoying i searched the steam workshop and found a mod to silence the groaning i found another mod that allowed me to use ingame character skins which i could then customize facially to create a unique character i preferred if you want to play as barbie im sure theres a mod for that as well it probably has a dreamhouse ie your house and tawny your horse integrated too i did a quick search on google and found this httpwwwyoutubecomwatchvxfps8kq7s1y ok ok this is not a steam workshop item but its funny skyrim is not a perfect game its biggest problem like oblivion is bugs i guess all those npcs various factions etc are going to glitch out sooner or later you will have problems that will prevent you from completing quests etc which would leave you gutted if they remained unsolved skyrim wiki sites have fixes for all the problems you will encounter i was easily able to find solutions to solve all of my bugs when they cropped up another issue with skyrim is keyboard control probably because its geared towards consoles it felt like keyboard control was an afterthought its not great but you get used to it oblivion was far superior in this area as mentioned skyrim is a deserving follow up to oblivion graphically skyrim is superior but oblivion still remains the finest moments ive had in gaming to follow up with an acceptable package after creating something so grand is a very tough ask theyve not only accomplished this in my opinion but they have excelled once again im blown away by a game skyrim does have alot of bugs normally for me that would be a game changer no punn intended the positives of skyrim completely supress any negatives aspects normally my viewpoint is heavily influenced by negative issues first rather than positive facets this speaks volumes about what skyrim got right ps i am not the one dancing shirtless at the end of that youtube video im bald
