910 summary amazing game with smart powerful and unique gameplay mechanics which are all complemented by colourful lore backstory and extensive rpg elements and mod support a very extensive variety of mods is already available as well as modding tools however players might occasionally be confronted with bugsglitches in the game which may hinder the game progression and lead to a negative gaming experience pros i captivating lore and backstory well written and directed quests with a fair amount of coherence on a logical basis ii simple yet powerful and versatile gameplay mechanics from combat and hunting to smithing and trading this game is easy to learn yet hard to master iii great for roleplaying the elder scrolls v  skyrim offers great character building tools to create your own personalized heroine or hero and begin conquering the land of skyrim iv moddable to the core infinite modding potential for extending the games capabilities and features such as additional races quests armour weapons and virtually anything else v optimized for most computer setups even if you have a medium to lowend computer skyrim will run quite decently given the relative reduction in graphical quality cons i extremely glitchybuggy in certain spots you can almost certainly rest assured that you will encounter a number of bugs throughout the game especially in quests  some of which are fixed by reverting to older game saves by installing unofficial patches released by the community others by performing specific actions or tricks eg using unrelenting force on an npc in an effort to reset them by uninstalling conflicting mods or by using certain commands eg setstage   yet some bugs and glitches may remain unfixable
