so obviously this game has so much to live up to and it delivers in literally every aspect of those expectations im a huge fan of tes so when i got my hands on this game the only thought was  score totally worth the money this review mainly consists of my playing on the console version but i picked it up for pc during the holiday sale and adding in the mod community only increases its replayability by countless hours days months no years my total time played on console is nearly 450 hours occassionally any game could get repetitive or boring and yes skyrim is no exception but this only takes place when you think youve done everything only to turn a corner and find 10 more hours of content you apparently were entirely oblivious to bethesda has done well to tuck extensive content into nearly every inch of the game world just waiting to be discovered the expansions were a welcome addition to the game especially since i was finally able to return to solstheim the only issue i walked away with was that the main storyline seemed short when compared with oblivion or morrowind but this may have just been because i blew through it out of pure excitement anyways the game is completely worth the price tag it was even worth the price tag of $60 at release clear and easiest 1010 i have ever had to give get the game side notes combat  910 not much improvement motionwise over oblivion but nonetheless engaging and awesome quests  1010 extensive numerous literally hundreds of quests rewarding and all enjoyable world  1010 definitely immersive never once did i feel a loss of involvement in the events unfolding around me enemies  1010 plenty of variations and to top it all off there are dragons just dragons if you take anything away from this just know dragons
