its rare when you find a game that attaches to you as well as skyrim over 5000 hours in between the xbox and my pc and the world still feels as fresh as ever as per the usual bethesda openworldcustomizablecharacterrpg your character has no voice but has dialogue options that allow you to depict what type of person your character is and how to respond to them skyrims lore is mainly what attached me to it for the world save for the main quest is incredibly rich in its scope granting the player countless hours and experiences simply by walking around if you truely want to explore skyrim the way it was meant to do not fast travel and see where your adventures take you the combat is nothing to write home about and stealth based characters outclass all other classes bar none especially on higher difficulties you cannot find the highest quality weapons until you are above level 46 rng dependent however they are more commonly found at higher levels at which point if your character is invested in smithing heshe can make the higher quality weapons than anything you can find in game to me this is one of the major downfalls of the game especially when you find a unique sword just to find out that you can make one that is twice as powerful and are in unlimited supply some of the decisions bethesda made regarding to dlc are rather offputting and i really wish they play tested these abit more being weaker in an exclusive form with a semipermanent follower that is unacceptable parts of the dlc are even lore breaking but i wont leave spoilers here what really increases this games replay value are the random encounters and of course usercreated content the modding community for skyrim is one of the largest in the video game industry from giant dlc sized mods that take place in new worlds to armor retexures and bunnyrabbit followers there is nothing you cannot find in terms of skyrim mods as always though make sure your computer can handle these mods as installing after market content is always on the user not the publisher skyrim however like most games of this scale im looking at you mass effect are not without their dissapointments there is no sense in scaling in terms of difficulty an archer on novice and an archer on legendary both have the same accuracy they just have exponential damagehealth scaling enemies level with you but this can be a blessing as well as a curse sure a level 32 bandit might be strong with that steel greatsword and that banded iron armor but you have a full set of ebony armor and an ebony war hammer as well as some restoration spells to heal you that level 32 bandit cant live a single hit from you and if he can you can stall him out with healing spells the ai have potions but never seem to use them the only truely challenging unmodded fight i can remember is the ebony warrior who you wont even see until your level 81 the differencies between classes are to0 far to make them all balanced but some of the perks just make certain builds untouchable example the last perk in the sneak tree allows you to conceal yourself while in combat sounds innocent enough but when you can crouch directly infront of someone and backstab them for 15x damage simply because the ai turns around and begins searching for you makes you borderline invincible especially considering there are only a few instances where you have to fight dragons the main quest especially the final boss is incredibly anticlimatic and has no more variety then any other standard battles you have in game at least they changed this for some of the dlcs but the lack of variety in the main quest compared to the rest of the game is heartbreaking and then there are the endless list of bugs that bethesda will never fix i wont list them here but as a tip never save with a crossbow in hands or inventory while crouched you will be locked in that position forever and you will know when its happened when your crosshair appears while you are crouched and you cannot stand up that list of cons however off putting they may seem should not stop you from purchasing the game it is well worth your time to play with or without mods i stress that mods greatly increase the enjoyment you will have in your game but to each hisher own skyrim has earned those awards by creating an excellent user experience perfect no nothing ever is is it close probably as close as any game will get
