so you want to know how good of a game skyrim is do you better question is why dont you already have it joking aside skyrim is one of those games which you can sink dozens if not hundreds of hours into and not get bored or even close to finishing the game and with a vast modding community both of these ideas get completely wiped off the board for me skyrim was my first elder scrolls game and since then i have played the other four i came into this game not being too big into the whole fantasy genre and when i came out that was completely turned around game universes dont get much bigger than the tes universe as skyrim is chokefull with lore in many forms the actual questlines fully readable books npc dialougem and much more while the games actual main plot isnt all that exiting imo centering around the return of the dragons in skyrim the world clearly makes up for it and alone could suck you into this game better yet you do not need to play the other tes games to understand skyrims story not saying you shouldnt play them of course graphically speaking skyrim is quite a nice game to look at with skyrims cold harsh northern landscape many different regions are seen with their own art style a castle fortress on the peak of a hill a sprawling city in the heart of a plain and a portside town in the middle of the arctic woods crappy descriptions aside youll see a lot here the game gives a very mysterious atmosphere as you venture through dark dungeons creep through enemy fortresses and just have a nice walk on the countryside the world may not feel all too alien but graphically its varied with its viking and medieval inspiration the only honest complaint i have is that small smaller items such as ropes arent that pretty to look at but mods always come into play with these problems gameplay oh boy skyrim is an openworld actionadventure rpg with sandbox elements mixed in as well you fight with swords battleaxes daggers from behind bows spells that can incinerate your foes and shouts that can hurl enemies far away while combat doesnt involve to many stratagies keep attacking your opponent while keep you distance or blocking their moves it is nonetheless enjoyable to fight through the many foes encountered magic on the other hand is a blast especially when combining spells or using them in conjunction with melee weapons ranged weapons are fun to use when being a stealthoriented character so there are a lot of choises you have when combating opponents as for enemy types theres a lot as well youll commonly fight bandits and wolves on the side of roads the undead draguar and skeletons in dungeons and even vampires and trolls when venturing out of course there are also the dragons these are fought by chance anywhere outside and usually take a lot of hits to take down unfortunately the stratagy of what should be a fun scenario is merely to attack the dragon when its on the ground and dodge its fire and to attempt to shoot it while in the air waiting for it to land again all dragons follow this system which is slightly disapointing as for exploring youll have a lot to find in skyrim new dungeons are scattered across the landscape as well as some truely unique characters that venture out one in particular all while listening to the games excellent soundtrack reflecting the mythical and harsh land that skyrim is i should mention that i have only scratched the surface of what the game has to offer and if youre interested get it and find out for yourself which will be quite a pleasant experience if you arent try it anyways you might find yourself immediatly immersed and impressed as i was if i had to rate skyrim i would give it a 9510 i should also add that skyrim has one of the best modding communities out there and even its own workshop here on steam even so id recommend going on nexus instead its just as easy has far more mods the biggest ones are on nexus nine times out of ten and doesnt have the file size restrictions like here on the workshop of course you should at least be familiar with what you think about the game before modding and going on from there mods i would recommend include skyui the vanilla games ui is ugly helgen reborn falskaar and frostfall which is on the workshop
