category score notes visuals 9 skyrim is a breathtaking and consistent world that makes you want to walk around just to see what else it has to offer open fields mountains and dragons flying in the distance truly make you feel as though youve been sucked into the world of the elder scrolls unfortunately the occasional but noticeable muddy textures can get in the way of that experience story 8 some quests are mundane and some set you on the path to greatness the game presents you with many choices most of which are just different means to the same end but some of which actually have an impact and will make you think twice attentive gamers will find all sorts of hidden stories told through notes subtle dialogue cues or even just the way objects are laid out in a certain room gameplay 7 finding the right difficulty setting can be a challenge in itself and some of the skill trees are significantly more powerful than others nonetheless there is plenty of variety and room for experimentation for how you want to play and plunging a sword through a dragons head rarely gets old the world comes especially alive when you avoid fasttravel sound 10 jeremy souls fourhour soundtrack adds a layer of emotion to your journey through skyrim that i didnt think possible until i heard that choir of over thirty people singing in the dragon tongue the music adds suspense melancholy and wonder to the world towns have their own unique themes as well mods 10 skyrim is a platform for an enormous amount of mods which has allowed it to remain relevant and popular even years after its release if youre just interested in prettying up your game enhancing the vanilla experience and making the game more immersive you can do that but if youd rather drive the batmobile to your sex dungeon and battle flying locomotives you can do that too overall 93 a fun rpg set in an immersive world with epic music and seemingly endless things to do mods transform it from a good game to one of the greatest ever and significantly increases replay value
