whenever you watch a video on youtube about skyrim you will bump into a person claiming that skyrim has been totally dumbed down and its a  game and bethesda sucks and believe me this works for any yt video about skyrim even ost vids type skyrim into youtube and watch the magic unfold whats interesting about this though is that these comments always turn into a heated war between skyrim lovers and the op who apparently hates skyrim and guess what both are right a year ago i watched samyouls video about the elder scrolls series being dumbed down although personally i felt that skyrim was one of the best games i have ever played i spent literally an entire summer day and night playing skyrim i clicked that little like button at the bottom of his vid and although i have played oblivion quite a lot and i own morrowind though i have yet to give that a serious try i did not like that video because i was flooded with nostalgia about how good and complex and detailed the older elder scrolls games were i clicked that because i did feel that skyrim was the most stripped game of the entire series conversations no longer had pages upon pages of topics to scroll through quests were no longer memorable we would never get another guild tale reaching the depths of the arena questline in oblivion and the oblivion gates all unique in their own ways were replaced by generic miniboss fights that happened whenever a dragon decided to attack you so why am i recommending this game because although its dumbed down skyrim is fun to play oblivion was indeed more complex than skyrim in many aspects custom spells and complicated alchemy just to name a few but at the same time oblivion was annoying to play i had to carry around extra weapons at all times in case they broke which was a nice but very annoying little feature present in oblivion and not in skyrim and although even as a whole skyrims mechanics could not reach the complexity found in rpgs like neverwinter nights it manages to string together all of its little parts and create something thats not complex or deep but is fun yes morrowind and oblivion were better more complex games yes they were deep in detail and lore but skyrim doesnt remove those aspects entirely they just sacrifice some of the less pleasing parts whoever needed 4 pieces of equipment to brew a potion to make an overall nicer and more pleasing tone to the game conversations feel natural im no longer talking to mr imperial city tour guide whenever i talk to a guard im talking to a tired man whos more happy in bed than patrolling around in the cold and probably cant really stop to chitchat anyway i think this all has to do with the evolution of the elder scrolls series daggerfall was in my opinion the pinnacle of the series in terms of complexity the entire yes entire continent of tamriel was rendered in the game and you could travel the entire continent though it would take hours to get to anywhere just like in real life morrowind sacrificed that feature to make the game a bit more accessible oblivion added fast travel and removed chancebased combat focusing more on skill and skyrim removes the complexities of most activities but i dont mind that nor do i protest that games i feel should be rated based on how fun they are to play i dont want to come home on a friday night just to spend hours worrying about how im going to get more repair hammers i want to come home on that friday night and play a good game in conclusion theres a difference between a good game and a fun game i feel that the elder scrolls series is slowly transitioning from being a good game to being a fun game but the thing that makes this series great is that its vital to maintain a balance between the two so no matter how dumbed down the game no matter how stripped the content bethesda is going to keep on making good elder scrolls games the lore demands it the story demands it the content demands it there is always going to be a good in a fun elder scrolls game skyrim is proof of that that there can be a balance between the two even if it means sacrificing a bit of one to rebalance the other skyrim is not a good game skyrim is a good and fun game 1001
