again your character starts off as a prisoner however they ruined the purpose of this tradition by later explaining what you were doing to get arrested the idea of being a prisoner in the earlier games was to allow the player to come up with their own backstory rather being forcefed one for your character but in skyrim they tell you that you were illegally crossing the border into skyrim just as a stormcloak squad was apprehended skyrim had a decent story but alduin as a main antagonist was lacking the depth and characteristics that previous ones like mehrunes dagon did in a land filled with dragons their best enemy for the plot was a slightly bigger dragon who could talk not very interesting if you ask me its just the fact that dragons are everywhere and then theres one that is sort of special but not by much the story and experience would have been more compelling if the characters in skyrim had any personality sure they have opinions on things like the civil war but everyone is so bland part of the problem is that everyone sounds alike there were a few unique npcs but that voice was only used for that one character such as clavicus vile but voices arent the only thing similar about the people like i said nobody has any personality the combat is very well executed the best combat in a firstperson rpg yet it has dual wielding you can have a spell and a sword and much more the thing that makes the fighting so unique is that hardly any games that ive played can pull it off like skyrim did and dual wielding is surprisingly rare in north american games so dont bring up any japanese ones not only do they tell you why your character was a prisoner but it doesnt make much sense if you play as a nord skyrim is your homeland why wouldnt you be allowed back there graphics although pointless in terms of a games value are quite polished in skyrim though i dont like the dull environment its just dark cave after dark cave identical nordic crypts and most of the land is just barren with snow and mountains i get that it is a snow province but theres no diversity in the environment as for mountains they just get in the way if you want to add mountains to a game make sure theyre easily climbable and have goodies or caves on top it would have been nice to add in a dead guy with tons of loot on him somewhere on the mountain who froze or something or at least a journal of a climber the leveling system is much better than their last elder scrolls game that makes me happy but some skills in skyrim feel tacked on or unfinished a big issue in skyrim is the enormous amount of glitches for example the legend of the red eagle quest you read about this ancient warrior bring his sword to a pedestal unlocking his burial site and then you fight him the problem is you can keep reading the book every time you complete the quest and it will start the quest all over again theres only one red eagle sword but doing it multiple times spawns multiple swords and its asking you to kill someone youve already killed like with oblivion some characters dont stay with the continuity long after the player ends the civil war for either side half of the characters in the game still talk about it as if its still happening i like all the guilds in skyrim besides companions but it feels overwhelming and contradictory if you join them all why would the listener of the dark brotherhood also be the leader of the companions or the archmage it wouldnt make too much sense thats why i dedicate one character to one guild in my games one minor thing i would like to note is the walkspeed you walk slower than everyone yet you run way faster than everyone its hard to keep pace and i dont like that i liked skyrim and i would put it above oblivion as a better game it has many things an rpg should have i rate this game a positive 6510 it doesnt get a higher rating because of lifeless characters boring and flat environment forgetting the whole reason as to why the player is always a prisoner in elder scrolls games and tons of glitches unlike oblivion i feel as though skyrim has replayability and not only would i recommend skyrim but i have started multiple characters all with their unique stories
