few games can compare in terms of content to skyrim this has been true since the first elder scrolls games which were also regarded as highly ambitious for their time dropping players into huge open worlds to explore with no shortage of quests to undertake and treasure to find the world changes around you depending on your actions npcs can die and never come back and a lot of dialog choices have drastic consequences the game is played mostly in 1stperson but can be switched to 3rdperson camera if you want depending on your preference singlehanded weapons allow you to use the rightmouse button to hold up a shield but there are also twohanded weapons as well as bows and crossbows various materials and enchantments with different effects mean a huge amount of customization can be done with your equipment the graphics are gorgeous very few locations look the same and it is a visual treat for the eyes with a massive variety of environments to explore the attention to detail is just mindblowing considering just how big the world is its matched by an equally epic soundtrack although i found that there wasnt enough diversity in the music and started to get tired of hearing some particular tracks multiple times unfortunately the game is crawling with bugs and i dont just mean giant spiders quest lines frequently get stuck assets will warp and spazz out all over the place the physics engine sometimes gives up and throws furniture everywhere some of these can actually prevent quests from being completed at all i recommend it anyway though because there just isnt anything out there quite like the elder scrolls games bugs aside it has enough unique content to keep you busy for a long time more than enough to justify the price tag of the legendary edition
