to begin with this one of the best if not even the very best game ive ever played graphics are gorgeous and breath taking game is based on open world system which is done perfectly thus there is option to fast travel it is actually very entertaining to travel on foot hence the landscapes are vivid and inimitable the land is actually full of believable and well made locations there is no feeling of boredness like in most of open world rpgs the whole game world is just so intense it lives on its own every npc does its daily basis and have a story to tell the main plot isnt maybe so gripping as in the plot based game however except the simple side quests the game consists few extensive and separate side story lines and those are usually better than the main quest line more over the game can take a lot of various mods which can improve or revamp any aspect of the game especially the enb mod is a must have if you are into visuals despite that game is almost the perfect in all aforementioned terms it has a few flaws firstly the leveling system although it works well up to about 30 lvl after that some enemies are just prevented from leveling thus fighting with them is becoming boring and the loot in this case is useless secondly combat styles are unbalanced for example magic is weak at the beginning then it gets overpowered and then again it becomes weaker than everything else because it cannot be improved after some point unlike the conventional combat methods which in theory can be upgraded to infinity another minor disadvantage is the ai enemies are truly dumb if it comes to sneaking they can take an arrow in the knee and after 15 seconds they say something like oh it must have been wind and of course like in every gigantic project it has to contain some bugs most of them have been fixed and there is no major bugs with completing the game like in fallout but sometimes some quest item gets stuck in inventory after finishing the quest and just clutters it but like i mentioned before game is extremely moddable so most of bugs can be prevented with mods and unbalanced combat system can be overhauled and if we consider that skyrim is so extensive game we can overlook those minor flaws and enjoy one of the greatest if not the very greatest game on this generation visuals visuals with enb believable world decent and vast dlcs incredibly moddable physics audio storyline well optimized performance in vanilla game  modding is not easy as it seems and it is time consuming however its worth it  ai  a couple of minor bugs  unbalanced combat system in vanilla game
