skyrim is one of those rpgs that could be classified as one in a million immediately after the brief opening scenes the game lets you go out into the enormous world and do whatever you like you can go directly to the main story or solely focus your attention of just the guilds or even spend 5 hrs picks flowers the game gives you absolute freedom to do whatever you want and thats rare in a game nowadays where even in rpgs there are hidden walls and linear questlines besides the quest the game has hundreds of locations for you to explore every dungeon is different in previous tes games most of the dungeons caves or whatever looked pretty much the same which wasnt a bad thing but each dungeon was hand crafted to be different humans beast creatures and dragons have set lvls meaning the stronger you get the easier theyll become this is a big difference compared to oblivion where everything you fought scaled with you that made the game much more difficult and annoying but skyrim allows you to go beast mode the higher you get making you feel like you really are the dragonborn then there are the mods mods mods and more mods i love them i have close to 50 mods on my game right now 34th of them are either texture or city mods when i say city mods i mean there are mods that allow you to change the way a city looks to give it a more vibrant and colorful feel bethesda did an amazing job with the cities but theyre pretty bare i have screenshots on my profile of just a few of the mods so as someone who has played skyrim on the xbox 360 the ps3 and the pc i can 100% say that this is one of the greatest rpgs that has ever been made you would have to be a fool to not try it it literally has something for everyones play style 1010
