introduction its rare for me to give a game a perfect score but skyrim is a real gem in this chapter of the elder scrolls saga you will probably end up investing hundreds of hours of your life to experience open world storytelling at its best bethesda did a flawless job immersing the player in countless diverse adventures from fighting dragons to dabbling with gods and none of these questlines ever lose their shine being an open world roleplaying game it goes without saying that skyrim provides a huge environment that you can explore at your own leisure however like its predecessors skyrim is not completely without flaw on rare occassion you might happen accross a technical glitch or two usually easily fixed by a mod but let me tell you firsthand that this is well worth the price in spite of its shortcomings skyrim is still the best game that i have ever played and it is impossible to see it as anything outside of a uniquely enchanting experience story really there is too much story to cover so here is the primary synopsis tamriel is a land brimming with danger in this masterpiece it was once prophesied that a dragon known as alduin would return to destroy the world it is up to the player to defeat the world eater before it is too late meanwhile there is a war brewing between the stormcloaks and the imperials in which the player can choose to involve themselves or remain neutral again this is a huge open world experience where you can safely ignore the main storyline for 80% or more of your gametime there is always stuff to do and you will never be bored gameplay there are several races and classes that you can pick from and there is something for everybody in the mix you can even mix races with their nondefault roles if you wish to experiment by default you can play a breton altmer high elf argonian bosmer wood elf dunmer dark elf imperial khajiit nord orsimer orc or redguard there are other races you could mod in however i feel the default races are perfect and found no need to do this myself it should be taken into consideration that each race starts with a different set of base stats the early game customization is wonderful and bethesda gives you a lot of options to work with i think the character customization in skyrim might just be one of my favourite elements so dont be afraid to add personality to your characters appearance classes are also extremely diverse and there is no right or wrong way to play them you could mix and match them and still be able to beat the game however some of the archetypes include twohanded warrior archer battlemage thief assassin warlock paladin and nightblade there are many places to read up on the archetypes so i wont flood this section with information  it should also be mentioned that the difficulty can be determined at any point in the game by the player i felt this was an extremely nice feature as i enjoy challenging gameplay i feel that skyrim is extremely well balanced and unless youre playing legendary never strays to the realm of impossibility even legendary creatures are beatable it just takes a lot more effort and strategy controls controls can be set through the settings menu and the default controls are really not so bad if youre anything like me however you might prefer the 360 controller approach and i am pleased to announce that this is entirely supported by skyrim it was no fuss for me to set it up and so i would say that the controls of this game are very user friendly  and in the end boil down to personal preference graphics i feel as though the graphic quality of skyrim has been highly praised elsewhere so permit me a moment to beat a dead horse the graphics in this game are true to detail and very indepth in other words worthy of the hype you can take your game a step further if you so desire by installing mods  as skyrim is a host to many of these personal preference improvements and remains highly customizable the aurora borealis which spans over tamriel at night is possibly the most beautiful feature to be found in the game the visuals and sounds are highly impressive on their own but when you mix them with exploration and discovery its only icing on the cake sound the sounds of skyrim feature an original score which i have been told reminds some people of oblivion the main theme is brilliant and has been covered countless times for those of you who might be interested the lyrics of the main theme is written in dragon language which sets it apart from the little tunes that you will hear the bards sing throughout the game replay value i have already replayed this game so many times and i guarantee you will too smolders note finally a note on modding this is extremely simple for those of you who have never modded before and even easier for those of you who have however you can easily fix a lot of the game bugs and glitches by use of these wonderful implementations made by other skyrim users it is also very simple to add other mods to your game such as immersive armors immersive creatures or immersive weapons all three are mods that i cannot live without i really want to take a moment to encourage you to check out the lorefriendly mods that might enhance your skyrim experience i hope this helped
