t save illegitemate maps skyrims map is an absolute collossus it is around the size of just cause 3s map but just medieval they put tons of detail in this map but if you want anything else of the map you can always mod it in fact you should mod it as long as your pc can handle it theres plenty of animals  creatures to kill loot and get xp points from you could go mining you could go on an adventure you could even ride a stallion to the tip of a mountain nearly touching the clouds while staring down below to see how far you have come but dont forget if you dissaprove then just mod it summary to sum skyrim up ive created a list or else id have to make 10 pages worth of a review on this superb game pros and cons pros excellent graphics giant number of modders and mods barely ever get bored theres so much things to do you can play the game without using a single cheat theres cheats if you dont like something  you could use a mod to change it legendary edition is worth the price dlc is worth the price massive map thousands of enemies quests that erent fully boring the gameplay is fun skill tree voice acting isnt terrible some funny dialouge lines you can install a mod such as wyrmstooth for a few more hours of fun the combat is pretty good you could buybuild your own house requires dlc if you already own dlc then mod the game you will feel as if its a completely different game you can change how things look such as changing the setting to extremely hot using mods you can mod skyrim cons no multiplayer skyrim might crash because of some mods 
