skyrim the game which rocked the world the unforgettable maxvonsydownarrated jeremysoulemusicpowered trailer that radiates awe an openworld experience of leading a virtual life of high adventure in a fantasy world i admit this was the first elder scrolls game that i played somehow all of the other games eluded me and i first seriously considered skyrim watching it played by the popular starcraft ii caster day[9]  this game as i later found out continues the elder scrolls formula which was evolved through several incarnations arena daggerfall morrowind oblivion perhaps its main defining characteristic is that instead of the experience system common for most rpgs your skill levels determine your character leveling and skill levels are raised by using them if you want to be a mage you will use your spells and level up if you want to be a warrior you will pick up your favorite type of weapon and swing it pick up a shield and block if you want to be a stealth character you will sneak simple and intuitive quests are as nonlinear as possible what this means is that you are most of the time not forced to do them or follow a specific order when completing them besides several larger questlines there are many small unrelated radiant quests which help flesh out the game and provide an even greater variety to already exciting core questlines there is a small caveat though the dark side of elder scrolls games are the bugs they happen to be something of a tradition with bethesda games and are even considered a fun factor many bugs were solved through various patches and expansions though and there are unofficial patches which are available through modding sites such as skyrim nexus [wwwnexusmodscom]  speaking of which another major aspect of skyrim are mods from different armor and weapons to textures and shaders and user interface this game has inspired many people to write dozens of mods since its release browsing through a plethora of available mods on some mod site alone could take you hours not that you will mind though skyrim is without any doubt one of the greatest rpgs and one of the greatest games made pick it up on a steam sale and play it you will completely lose track of time and you will love it
