skyrim is quite simply put one of the best rpgs ever made the game is absolutely massive ive put in just over 100 hours so far in the last week or so and im probably only about 2025% through the game there arent many games that give you 300 or more hours of single player gameplay in a single game and this game has to top the list the graphics are amazing and very beautiful the open outdoor world is massive and allows you to freely roam wherever you like with no artificial restrictions except perhaps the boundaries of the map which ive never reached in over 100 hours of gameplay unlike most other dungeons & dragons style rpgs that follow a more pen and paper based approach to painstakingly creating a character and assigning dozens of numerical character attributes and managing them over time skyrim is incredibly immersive by taking a different approach to character building and evolution in skyrim you choose your characters race from about 10 or so different races but you do not choose a character class or assign attribute points etc instead you start out as a newbie character with no real skills other than a few benefits attributed to the race youve chosen such as being naturally resistant to fire or whatever from that point on your character evolves based on how you choose to play the character via ingame decisions you take whatever weapons or skills you choose to start using to solve problems with you will evolve those skills and become better at using them for example if you use a bow and arrow a lot your archery skill will improve and you will essentially become an archer by way of doing it rather than via artificial preselection if you choose to cast spells and do other forms of magic such as staves etc then you will start to become a mage but nothing holds you back from specializing in as many things as you want this really makes the game incredibly flexible and tears down artificial class boundaries of the traditional rpg my character is a female high elf which has evolved via gameplay to become a thiefarchermage for example but the possibilities are endless and it allows for characters that are much more unique just as in the real world and not boxed into one well defined role the game is infinitely moddable also and has an incredibly rich modding community with mods that add new content and quests new items objects decorations new armour and weapons adult content and eyecandy humour and a multitude of other enhancementsaddons quite simply put this is one of the largest and incredibly fun to play rpgs ever made and any fan of rpgs who has not yet played skyrim should definitely get this game and prepare to set aside hundreds of hours for entertainment
