i feel like ive got enough hours under my belt to put together a fair review of this game so lets hope itll be a useful one at the time of leaving this review ive clocked 199 hours but ive played this game for a fair amount of time in offline mode on top of that probably about 20 hours or so so what was i doing on this game for all that time the first 30 or so were pretty much a waste though this isnt really the fault of the game i went into this game not really knowing what to expect as i knew little to nothing about the world of elder scrolls i was more eager to just play than i was to pay attention to the characteristics and powers of each race so i ended up choosing a nord and progressing down an allrounder character route investing skill points in a bunch of random skill trees while the idea of being an allrounder and being able to approach combat however you choose might sound appealing in this game it felt really boring but thats not necessarily a bad thing it encouraged me to start fresh and being partial to the magic and spells in this game i decided to play through as a high elf mage and found this route to be right for me and overall pretty enjoyable however sometimes the game crashes without warning and may crash again at the exact same point the next time you attempt it which can be extremely irritating and make gameplay feel beyond tedious also if id played this game on a console instead of pc im not really sure how id feel about it for two reasons the first is console commands which among other things allow you to perform actions which should have been features implemented in the base game available from a low level such as allowing you to remove perks youve chosen and select different ones in their place the second is mods the modding community has produced a whole variety of very useful mods which fix bugs balance combat and leveling and add in new features some of which should have been there in the first place  overall making the game a much more enjoyable experience all in all i do like this game but if i didnt have access to console commands and mods i probably wouldnt like it all that much
