this review was made with 244 hours playtime on steam and much more off steam i would like to begin by giving a quick overview of the game in the elder scrolls v skyrim you presume the role of the dragonborn destined to do all sorts of things from exploring dungeons to sleeping in inns to eating sweetrolls whats wrong someone stole your sweetroll never mind because this is the fifth game in the series that is the five main games in the series arena daggerfall morrowind oblivion and of course skyrim skyrim itself takes place in the northerntundras of tamriel a wartorn land split by a civil war and infested with bandits right now thats all finished this time ill try something different with the reviewing system ill split everything up gameplay 710 a good gameplay system depending on who you are a massive change from morrowind and a partial continuation of the general feel of oblivion skyrim has some new gameplay mechanics that is the perk trees of each individual skill the way those skills work and interact with the game on a mechanical and general level and the general leveling of each statskill the reason this hasnt gotten a 1010 for all the new gameplay mechanics is mostly due to the fact that skyrim was to put it bluntly but truthfully dumbed down by which i mean made easier made simpler made more mash this and repeat that the late game classarchetypes end up being literally that  as a mage stunlocking is all you do as a rogue stealth kills with insane damage levels is all you do as a warrior potions potions potions potions potions potions oh and more potions  is all you do this can all be fixed by the community in fact it has been fixed by the community as youll find out soon enough story 510 ah quite the letdown to be honest whether or not you find the storyline of the game interesting or not is truly dependant on your preference without spoiling anything the most i can say is the storyline of skyrim was a huge downgrade from that of say morrowind oblivion even not that i much enjoyed that either there are a few plotholes here and there and in general the whole storylines is pretty repetative and unengaging it should also be noted that again cured by the community there is very little choice within the storylines which could cause them to become boring after a short while yes i understand this isnt just a problem with skyrim but im reviewing skyrim combat 410 as earlier mentioned the combat mechanics of the game are rather basic and simplistic this may not affect you but after a while when youre stuck doing the exact same thing or mashing the exact same buttons with weapons and tactics that can beat the highest game difficulties masterlegendary as if they were on the lowest things do tend to get boring and tedious the lategame of this is horrible  but then again starting the game over a couple of hundred thousand million billion trillion times never hurt anyone trust me ive been there and ive done that no really  really but to be serious the combat system in the vanilla game is very repetative and thus very tedious andor boring but some people enjoy that kind of thing the simplistic side to combat where you dont have to care about much else other than doing the same things over and over to max out your characters so good for you my completionistchums that is unless youre a completionist who doesnt like having to do that kind of thing graphics look im a person who plays a game for the game  not the graphics otherwise for all those pixelterrorists heh no ok sorry out there there are plenty of graphics mods all over and even bethesdas own high resolution texture pack the world 710 skyrims world rather coincidentally not really named skyrim is a tundra landscape with many mountains and valleys rivers and lakes frozen seas and the like a vast land with alot to discover explore and contemplate from beautiful scenes to rough areas to scary crypts and tombs  skyrim has it all pretty much barring a few exceptions if you can see it 