 this review is lengthy if you just want the summary scroll to the bottom if you want a breakdown of the items listed feel free to read all of it either way youll get an accurate honest review of the game if you want a simple review scroll down to the bottom after owning the game on both pc and console and after creating a myriad of characters ranging from the buffest most brutal warriors to the most timid and sly pickpocketers i can say that this game is hands down amazing its been three years since the release of the elder scrolls v skyrim 111111 and it has captured my attention ever since most of my hours were logged on console before i came to my better senses got a pc and grabbed the legendary edition on sale for 20 bucks this review will detail the following  base game  combat  types of characters and races  variety of mods  recommendations and conclusions about the game note no storyline other than nonspoiler mentions will be made in this review so dont worry about that the base game itself is very satisfying the staggering amount of side quests individuals random events and items gives the game an almost endless replayability the skill trees are straightforward and easily read and used the inventory is very simple yet as many people can understand the inventory has no search bar making searching for a quest item a little more challenging in a cluttered inventory the inventory is sorted alphabetically so the worst you have to do is scroll down a list of infinite keys letters from friends death threats and other sorts of nonsuch which isnt really bad side quests are very rewarding and fun you never know if the stranger who is stranded on the side of the road needing help with his wagon is a simple person in need of help or a runaway murderer the leveling of the skill tree can go on forever and so can the main level which used to be 81 but patch 19 allowed you to make any skill that is level 100 into a legendary perk resetting its skill to 15 and letting you earn an infinite amount of xp from your skill trees the main level can even go above level 252 so no need to worry about capping out on a level because your skill trees that made your character a thief archer warrior etc were already in other words unlimited leveling combat is very rewarding and fun it can be challenging at times but thank talos you have a million and one potions of archery alchemy health stamina magika and lockpicking to see you through it fighting one on one is simple enough but one against several is challenging and can try the patience and skill of even the most battlehardened warriors each type of character has a variety of ways of handling multiple opponents although some vary in efficiency aoe area of effect spells work or a sweeping blow from your battleaxe or just quick jabs from a knife to each opponent the choice is yours from my personal experience keep in mind this is what i like and not what is best statistically i have found that archery or a sword and shield is preferable to magic or twohanded weapons archery lets you pick off target from a distance giving them a lot of damage shields block a lot of damage and after attacks you can let out a killing blow of your own magic can summon minions of the dead ice fire etc as your own personal posse two handed weapons deal massive amounts of damage which makes up for their bulkiness armor usually is a preference of the player not bound to one fighting style or the other also fus roh dah as for races each race is specialized towards a certain type of fighter for example you typically wouldnt take a high elf as a warrior or a redguard as a magician but both are available to you if you so desire the races are listed below  nord primarily two  handed warriors  imperial primarily shield users  breton usually mages  argonian primarily thievesrestoration or alteration mages  wood elf primarily thievesarchers  high elf primarily mages  dark elf primarily mages  khajiit primarily thieves  orc primarily warriors  redguard primarily warriors classes warrior very strong very tough to kill they are usually slow but devastating to enemies use heavy armor mages cunning and powerful they cant take many hits but can conjure things up to take hits for them and can have a very diverse selection of spells to use at any time use light armor with spell enchants thieves sly and deadly use one handed weapons which are usually daggers they prefer to stay hidden and make their money off of stealing items from peoples homes or pockets wear light armor that is usually of a material like leather archers precise and meticulous stay back and engage fights first with well placed shots use one handed weapons and light armor for when they cant pick people off fast enough the moment youve all been waiting for mods the amount of mods that have been created for skyrim are astounding graphics can be improved glitches can be fixed items added people added places added actions added and much more the steam workshop has a great deal of mods that work on their own and some that just dont work at all these mods can be managed easily on the launch menu of the game some of these mods require other mods that help run them these helping mods can come from the workshop or the skyrimnexus which is a huge modding community posting mods for skyrim users to enjoy hello to everyone who just wants to know about the damn game and not all this information also hello to the people who actually read my entire review in which case thanks anyway here goes the elder scrolls v skyrim is a fantastic game the diversity of all aspects of this game is unique and hard to find in other titles should you get it yes should you get the legendary edition hell yes but get it on sale because skyrim goes on sale frequently overall great game must get any questions about the diversity of the game please consult the novel above this paragraph ps all hail todd howard and jeremy soule
