to be honest if youre reading skyrim reviews its not because youre on the fence about actually buying the game so i dont feel the need to write some form of lengthy review of the most well known rpg of the past decade edit apparently valve removed monetization of modsfor now i am keeping my editorial rant up but changing my recommendation because frankly skyrim really is just a damn fine game the language of the pr release however suggests that they are going to come out something else so becoming complacent in victory would be an extremely bad idea for a sense of context i want to point out i am all for mod makers being compensated for their work through donations i have no problem donating money to mod makers if they provide me with a worthwhile addition to my game and give this addition free of upfront charge i understand the amount of work some of these people put into their mods and i wholeheartedly think they deserve something for their passion and work turning mods into dlc is however insulting to not only me as a gamer but the mod maker as they become an exploited worker this doesnt have to be the case they can all make money and make people happy at the same time if they werent so fcking greedy to start with if steam radically changes the system to be only donations only donations taking less then 20% for themselves and bethesda then all involved would make far more money total and come out of this looking flawless from a pr point of view as an example i have bought premium currency or what have you from good free to play games i have enjoyed as you can see in my profile i have played a lot of warframe and have donated a lot of money to the company by now its probably a few hundred of dollars over the years which yes is a lot of money to most people because they are offering me an ever improving game completely free and i think they deserve something if warframe had demanded a subscription or money up front they would of made nothing off me as i never would of played it to begin with there are a lot of gamers like me gamers that have funded plenty of free to play games like dwarf fortress have given money to the humble bundles far exceeding the minimal amount and funded plenty of games on kickstarter due to nothing more then altruism and a belief in a fellow gamers passion to improve the industry a modding paywall however feels as though valve bethesda and even a few modders themselves are  on the very notion of what makes pc gaming great it is insulting to me as a gamer it is insulting to us all as a culture and it is something that should not be tolerated with the way the system exists now or rather how it existed before the rollback i will not be buying games through steam unless i have no choice and i will never pay for a mod ever i am more then happy to send a donation to a few modders who do exceptional work interesting npcs comes to mind but any modder who hides their content behind a paywall will lose my respect and any chance of ever getting money off me id also like to point out that monetizing and releasing total conversions which create an entirely new game using an existing engine such as garys mod and dayz are not the same thing as paying for skyrim mods i cant fathom why certain people involved in this side of modding the need to voice their opinion when they clearly have no idea what theyre talking about
