the elder scrolls v skyrim is the only quality variant of a lord of the rings video game that it isnt trying to be nor actually is one its a bit of a medieval simulator with its own cannon and lore with several plot lines taking up the majority of your time alongside the numerous expansion content and side quest lines that allow you to truly become your own character whether that be a modern robin hood or the next incarnation of merlin some of these quest lines arent the longest and some of them are quite repetitive but many of them allow you to become something of yourself high and mighty and powerful even though not that much significance is made of it in comparison to the fact youre the next dragonborn and the loot throughout the majority of these lines only getting you by with my only complaint there really being the fact that i did not have the freedom to choose where to place what quest line and where and eventually not even finishing the dragonborn dlc quest line due to boredom mechanics are plentiful in skyrim stats management is simple and only consists of health stamina and magicka which includes powers and dragon shouts too and an ability to upgrade a whole host of skills through the indepth specialised tree for them if you prefer something other than magic like me you can go and be an archer with different types of arrows and bows to fire them with upgrading and enchanting throughout or you can wave a sword around like an unbreakable stick fast travel is also a thing which kind of removes some of the immersion from the game but nonetheless getting you throughout the vast world you can trade and sell your old items as you upgrade enchant and move on through variant merchants using the same simplistic menu system that gets you lost the more items you carry using commands through the console is also a big help and on computer its rather a present from the heavens due to many of the impractical bugs causing you large annoyance are either fixable or well avoidable  but if you use the commands to cheat it really ruins the experience i got bored of the game once i did this it became less of a challenge to achieve something gain something or complete something concluding this game was a real blast for the hundred or more hours i poured into it and it really allows you to get immersed and continue playing just one more dungeon yada yada you really must avoid cheating though  curiosity will ruin it for you
