well what can i say  i love the elder scrolls series and i love skyrim as one of the series i love oblivion and morrowind the elder scrolls series portrays a very realistic view on the fantasy world many years ago it does this by stunning graphics  you do not need an amazing graphics card to run this game people will recommend the gtx 670 but i have a 7770 and the game looks stunning on ultra and you can also download the hd texture mods this will show a much better graphical content but with the hd texture mod somethings have not been worked on as much as somethings else ie the rocks in caves compared to the sky i believe this is because the sky is viewed more than the rocks inside of caves good physics  i know this game has good physics i can tell because i have played all the other elder scrolls and on morrowind the physics were as good as they can be in 2001 oblivion again the physics were as good as they can be in 2009 and possibly we could think the same about skyrim in a few years time nevertheless the physics are very good and this contributes to the brilliant graphics that this game provides the story  although this game can be played after the first 5 quests i believe very different you can choose to do quests or you can explore and hunt and explore caves then once you have explored the places that the map will let you you can then do quests in different parts of skyrim ie dawnstar markarth morthalriftensolitudewhiterunwindhelmwinterhold and falkreath but withing these constituencies there are towns that the quests are allocated the whole game  with all of the brilliant physics and the stunning graphics even without the hd texture mod this game you can play for hours on end and just forget about the real world and create and play your own fantasy and take risks and use logic overall  the game is brilliant as i have explained above the graphics and the physics make the game much more enjoyable just like any other game  1010
